Peggy square
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a knitted square of about 5 inches size to be sewn to others to make rugs etc., for poor people.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1934 Aunt Molly's Children's Session on 2YA Wellington ca1951 21st May Corresp. School on radio 2YA. Peggy squares for rugs for displaced children.
